==English==
=== Etymology ===
Latin ''[[iuvenilia]],'' neuter plural of ''[[iuvenilis]]'' “of or pertaining to youth.”

=== Noun ===
'''juvenilia''' ''plural'' or ''collective singular''
# [[works|Works]] produced during an [[artist]]'s or [[author]]'s [[youth]].
# Works [[suit]]ed or [[produce]]d for the young.

